ough it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Roger BROOKS was born as the son of William Brooks and Unknown. He married Agnes De Covele about 1139. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","ABT 1140":"umbes 1140","1090":"1090","Abt 1139":"umbes 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","ABT 1140":"noin 1140","1090":"1090","Abt 1139":"noin 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1120–Female":"1120–Décédée","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1090–Male":"1090–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","ABT 1140":"environ 1140","1090":"1090","Abt 1139":"environ 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Roger BROOKS est né, fils de William Brooks et Unknown. Il a épousé Agnes De Covele environ 1139. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1120–Female":"1120–Verstorben","1140–Male":"1140–Verstorben","1090–Male":"1090–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","ABT 1140":"um 1140","1090":"1090","Abt 1139":"um 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Roger BROOKS wurde, als Sohn von William Brooks und Unknown geboren. Er hat um 1139 Agnes De Covele geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 